quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,138,"And We made the Children of Israel pass over the sea, then they came upon a people who were devoted to some human-shaped idols of theirs. They said, “O Moses, make for us a god as they have gods.” He said, “You are truly speaking ignorantly.”"
  7,139,"“What these people are concerned with is surely doomed to perdition, and whatever they used to do is false.”"
  7,140,"He said, “Shall I seek for you a god other than Allah when He has favored you over all communities?”"
  7,141,"And recall how We{1}savedyou from Pharaoh’s folk who inflicted upon you an evil punishment, relentlessly killing{2}your sons and keeping your women alive<i>(in bondage) </i>. And in that was a great test from your Lord.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “And recall when He saved you…”],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Nafie’ read it as: “…evil punishment, killing your sons…”]
  7,142,"And We appointed{1}forMoses thirty nights, and completed them with ten. And thus the time appointed by his Lord{2}was forty nights. And Moses said to his brother Aaron: “Take my place among my people, and be upright, and do not follow the way of the corrupters.”",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Abu Amr, Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “And We promised Moses thirty nights,”],footnotes:2:[A grammatical shift from 1<sup>st</sup> person to 3 person to 3<sup>rd</sup> person. person.]
  7,143,"And when Moses came for Our appointment and his Lord<sup>d </sup>spoke to him, he said, “My Lord, let me see—to look upon You.” He said, “You will not see Me, but look at the mountain—if it<i>(still) </i>resides in its place, you will see Me.” But when his Lord manifested Himself to the mountain, He turned it into rubble{1}, and Moses fell down unconscious. Then when he recovered, he said, “Highly Exalted are You; I have indeed repented to you, and I am the first of the believers.”",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 1<sup>st</sup> person to 3 person to 3<sup>rd</sup> person. person.],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…He turned it into flattened land,”]
